column4: Breakingviews - Apple’s less-is-more vibe bodes well for profit
column5: NEW YORK (Reuters Breakingviews) - Apple has long followed Mies van der Rohe’s design precept that “less is more.” Now it’s doing the same financially. The company sold fewer iPhones for more money in the last quarter  it reported on Thursday. That raises fears that the company is losing its innovation edge. But that’s OK – persuading customers to pay more arguably requires as much genius as getting people to adopt the technology in the first place.
